Always use Context7 MCP when I need library/API documentation, code generation, setup or configuration steps without me having to explicitly ask.

When working with Python libraries (FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Panel, Pydantic), automatically fetch documentation from Context7.

When working with TypeScript/JavaScript libraries (Next.js, React, pnpm, Poetry), automatically fetch documentation from Context7.

For the Financial Checker project, prioritize documentation for:
- FastAPI (backend API framework)
- SQLAlchemy (database ORM)
- Panel/HoloViz (current UI framework)
- Next.js 14+ (target frontend framework)
- React 18+ (target UI library)
- Pydantic (data validation)
- MySQL/SQLite adapters
